race.comment: They should go very hard and happy to trust the premier rider will let it all unfold on ELITE BEAU (8). Made debut with a fast finishing win then went straight into the Perth Stakes and ran below best. Given a break and presents on the back of two sharp trial wins. Likely to stalk and hit the line hard.  XENTARO (7) won two on end then was sixth but beaten less than two lengths last start. Another who will sit back and charge home late.  PROMISING (5) had just one run last time in when struggled on heavy ground and went back out to the paddock. Fitter for two trials and despite the draw will take catching. SPICY THANG (9) gave a sight but faded late last time in richer company. Can give a sight this line-up with the light weight. COONDLE (3) has had plenty of tries but better than recent form. Suited here and can give a sight off the low draw.
